Russian businessman Said Kerimov has resigned from the board of directors of gold mining company Polyus. His company Wandle Holdings has also sold about 40.8-million shares in Polyus to Akropol Group. As a result, Kerimov reduced his interest in Polyus from 76.34% to 46.35%. Polyusâ€™ principal operations are located in Siberia and the Russian Far East.